    {
      "id": "0522b6a9_a3031e31",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/spi/impl/CpsDataPersistenceServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 494,
      "message": "No, even if we keep the existing method, the new method should still be changed. It's not consistent with existing.\n\nThe existing method takes xpath and a map of leaves. Since DataNode contains those fields:\n  public class DataNode {\n    private String xpath;\n    private Map<String, Serializable> leaves;\n    ...\n  }\n\nthe existing method is equivalent to this:\n  void updateDataLeaves(String dataspaceName, String anchorName, DataNode updatedDataNode)\n\nThus the new one should be:\n  void batchUpdateDataLeaves(String dataspaceName, String anchorName, Collection<DataNode> updatedDataNodes);\n\nThis is also similar to other batch operations like updateDataNodesAndDescendants, which has this signature:\n   void updateDataNodesAndDescendants(String dataspaceName, String anchorName, Collection<DataNode> updatedDataNodes);",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2023-05-03 09:39:01.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f1d30a36_b989b775",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "efaaeffb_841cbad0",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/spi/impl/CpsDataPersistenceServiceImpl.java",
